Key Trends
1.	Digital Wound Management
The adoption of digital wound care platforms for remote monitoring is transforming patient care, particularly for those managing chronic conditions.
2.	Focus on Biologics
Biologics such as growth factors and engineered tissues are gaining traction due to their ability to enhance healing and minimize scarring.
3.	Sustainability
Increased focus on eco-friendly materials in wound care products aligns with broader environmental goals.
